  • Constructor Details

    • Booking

      public Booking​(User userID, Room roomNumber, Module moduleID, java.util.Calendar startTime, int duration, java.util.Calendar date, boolean isSociallyDistant, java.lang.String bookingType, int numPeople)
      This is the constructor method that compiles the parameter values with the field variables.
      Parameters:
      userID - this represents the user who booked the room.
      roomNumber - this represents the room used in the booking.
      moduleID - this represents the module taught during the booking.
      startTime - this represents the start time for a room.
      duration - this represents how long the room is booked for (in number of hours).
      date - this represents the date when the room will be used.
      isSociallyDistant - this represents whether the room is used socially distant.
      bookingType - this represents the type of booking (Lecture, Practical, Other).
      numPeople - this represents the number of people in the room.
